---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import AffiliateLink from '../../components/AffiliateLink.astro';

const meta = {
  title: 'Framer vs Durable.co: Which AI Website Builder is Better?',
  description: 'I tested both Framer and Durable for 3 weeks each. One is a full website builder with AI features. The other is AI-first with limited scope. Here\'s the detailed comparison.',
  image: '/og-image.svg',
  keywords: ['Framer vs Durable', 'Durable.co alternatives', 'Framer review', 'AI website builder comparison', 'best AI website builder 2025'],
};
---

<Layout {...meta}>

  <!-- Hero -->
  <section class="bg-[#FEF9F3] py-12 sm:py-16 md:py-20">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4">
      <p class="text-[10px] sm:text-xs font-black text-[#E07A5F] mb-4 tracking-[0.3em] uppercase">
        6 Weeks Testing · Real Projects Built · Detailed Comparison
      </p>

      <h1 class="text-3xl sm:text-4xl md:text-5xl lg:text-6xl font-black mb-6 leading-tight">
        Framer vs Durable.co
      </h1>

      <h2 class="text-xl sm:text-2xl md:text-3xl text-gray-700 mb-8 font-bold">
        Website Builder Showdown
      </h2>

      <p class="text-lg sm:text-xl md:text-2xl text-gray-700 mb-8">
        I tested both Framer and Durable for 3 weeks each, building real projects. One is a full website builder with AI features. The other is AI-first with limited scope. Here's what actually matters.
      </p>

      <div class="bg-[#E07A5F]/10 border-2 border-[#E07A5F] rounded-xl p-6">
        <p class="font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">
          Quick answer: Framer for complete websites, Durable for quick landing pages.
        </p>
        <p class="text-gray-700">
          But they're solving different problems. Framer is a Webflow competitor with AI. Durable is an AI landing page generator. Read on for the breakdown.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Quick Comparison -->
  <section class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 py-12 border-t border-gray-200">
    <h2 class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl md:text-4xl font-black mb-8 text-gray-900">
      Quick Comparison
    </h2>

    <div class="overflow-x-auto">
      <table class="w-full border-collapse">
        <thead>
          <tr class="bg-gray-100">
            <th class="border border-gray-300 px-4 py-3 text-left font-bold">Feature</th>
            <th class="border border-gray-300 px-4 py-3 text-left font-bold">Framer</th>
            <th class="border border-gray-300 px-4 py-3 text-left font-bold">Durable</th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr>
            <td class="border border-gray-300 px-4 py-3 font-semibold">Product Type</td>
            <td class="border border-gray-300 px-4 py-3"><span class="text-green-600 font-bold">Full website builder</span></td>
            <td class="border border-gray-300 px-4 py-3">AI landing page generator</td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="bg-gray-50">
            <td class="border border-gray-300 px-4 py-3 font-semibold">Best For</td>
            <td class="border border-gray-300 px-4 py-3"><span class="text-green-600 font-bold">Complete websites, complex projects</span></td>
            <td class="border border-gray-300 px-4 py-3">Single landing pages</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td class="border border-gray-300 px-4 py-3 font-semibold">AI Features</td>
            <td class="border border-gray-300 px-4 py-3">Good (AI-assisted building)</td>
            <td class="border border-gray-300 px-4 py-3"><span class="text-green-600 font-bold">Excellent (AI-first)</span></td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="bg-gray-50">
            <td class="border border-gray-300 px-4 py-3 font-semibold">CMS / Blogging</td>
            <td class="border border-gray-300 px-4 py-3"><span class="text-green-600 font-bold">Built-in CMS</span></td>
            <td class="border border-gray-300 px-4 py-3">Not supported</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td class="border border-gray-300 px-4 py-3 font-semibold">Ecommerce</td>
            <td class="border border-gray-300 px-4 py-3"><span class="text-green-600 font-bold">Full support</span></td>
            <td class="border border-gray-300 px-4 py-3">Not supported</td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="bg-gray-50">
            <td class="border border-gray-300 px-4 py-3 font-semibold">Design Flexibility</td>
            <td class="border border-gray-300 px-4 py-3"><span class="text-green-600 font-bold">Extremely high</span></td>
            <td class="border border-gray-300 px-4 py-3">Limited</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td class="border border-gray-300 px-4 py-3 font-semibold">Learning Curve</td>
            <td class="border border-gray-300 px-4 py-3">1-2 hours</td>
            <td class="border border-gray-300 px-4 py-3"><span class="text-green-600 font-bold">5 minutes</span></td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="bg-gray-50">
            <td class="border border-gray-300 px-4 py-3 font-semibold">Pricing</td>
            <td class="border border-gray-300 px-4 py-3">$15-40/month</td>
            <td class="border border-gray-300 px-4 py-3">$0-20/month</td>
          </tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- What Framer Is -->
  <section class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 py-12 border-t border-gray-200">
    <h2 class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl md:text-4xl font-black mb-8 text-gray-900">
      What Framer Actually Is
    </h2>

    <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 mb-6">
      Framer is a full website builder. Think "Webflow but easier" with AI features sprinkled in. You can build anything: landing pages, blogs, ecommerce sites, portfolios—whatever.
    </p>

    <div class="bg-purple-100 border-l-4 border-purple-600 rounded-r-xl p-6 my-8">
      <p class="font-bold mb-3">What I built in Framer (3 weeks):</p>
      <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-700">
        <li>• Complete agency website (10 pages)</li>
        <li>• Blog with CMS for easy content management</li>
        <li>• Ecommerce store with 20 products</li>
        <li>• Portfolio site with case studies</li>
        <li>• SaaS product landing page + documentation</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 mb-6">
      <strong>The AI part:</strong> Framer has AI features to help you build faster. "Generate a hero section" or "Suggest a color palette." But it's still fundamentally a drag-drop builder with AI assistance.
    </p>

    <h3 class="text-xl font-black mb-4 mt-10">What Framer Does Best</h3>

    <div class="bg-green-50 rounded-xl p-6 my-8">
      <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-700">
        <li><strong>Complete websites</strong> — Not just landing pages. Full multi-page sites with navigation.</li>
        <li><strong>CMS and blogging</strong> — Built-in content management system. Real blogging capabilities.</li>
        <li><strong>Ecommerce</strong> — Full online store with payments, inventory, etc.</li>
        <li><strong>Design flexibility</strong> — Once you learn it, you can build anything.</li>
        <li><strong>Professional results</strong> — Sites look hand-designed, not AI-generated.</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- What Durable Is -->
  <section class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 py-12 border-t border-gray-200">
    <h2 class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl md:text-4xl font-black mb-8 text-gray-900">
      What Durable Actually Is
    </h2>

    <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 mb-6">
      Durable is an AI-first landing page generator. You tell it about your business, it generates a complete landing page in 60 seconds. No drag-drop, no learning curve. Just AI generation.
    </p>

    <div class="bg-purple-100 border-l-4 border-purple-600 rounded-r-xl p-6 my-8">
      <p class="font-bold mb-3">What I built in Durable (3 weeks):</p>
      <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-700">
        <li>• 12 landing pages for different business ideas</li>
        <li>• Each took 10-15 minutes from idea to published</li>
        <li>• Most were single-page sites (Durable's strength)</li>
        <li>• Copy quality was excellent</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 mb-6">
      <strong>The catch:</strong> Durable is limited to landing pages. No blogging. No ecommerce (beyond simple payments). No multi-page sites. It does one thing incredibly well.
    </p>

    <h3 class="text-xl font-black mb-4 mt-10">What Durable Does Best</h3>

    <div class="bg-green-50 rounded-xl p-6 my-8">
      <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-700">
        <li><strong>Speed</strong> — Landing page in under 15 minutes. Unmatched.</li>
        <li><strong>Copy quality</strong> — AI writing is excellent. Persuasive, specific, on-brand.</li>
        <li><strong>Ease of use</strong> — Zero learning curve. Anyone can use it.</li>
        <li><strong>Beautiful defaults</strong> — Generated pages look good immediately.</li>
        <li><strong>Hosting included</strong> — One-click publish, no setup.</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- The Fundamental Difference -->
  <section class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 py-12 border-t border-gray-200">
    <h2 class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl md:text-4xl font-black mb-8 text-gray-900">
      The Fundamental Difference
    </h2>

    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 my-8">
      <div class="bg-gray-100 rounded-xl p-6">
        <h3 class="font-bold mb-3">Framer's Approach</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">"Here's a powerful tool. Build whatever you want. AI will help you along the way."</p>
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-700">
          <li>• Tool-first, AI-assisted</li>
          <li>• Unlimited flexibility</li>
          <li>• Learning curve required</li>
          <li>• Can build anything</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-gray-100 rounded-xl p-6">
        <h3 class="font-bold mb-3">Durable's Approach</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">"Tell me about your business. I'll build your landing page for you."</p>
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-700">
          <li>• AI-first, tool-assisted</li>
          <li>• Limited scope (landing pages)</li>
          <li>• Zero learning curve</li>
          <li>• Does one thing perfectly</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>

    <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 mb-6">
      <strong>The key insight:</strong> Framer is for people who want to build. Durable is for people who want to be done.
    </p>
  </section>

  <!-- Real Project Examples -->
  <section class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 py-12 border-t border-gray-200">
    <h2 class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl md:text-4xl font-black mb-8 text-gray-900">
      Real Project Examples
    </h2>

    <h3 class="text-xl font-black mb-4 mt-10">Project 1: Agency Website</h3>

    <div class="bg-gray-100 rounded-xl p-6 my-8">
      <p class="font-bold mb-3">Framer approach:</p>
      <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-700">
        <li>• <strong>Time:</strong> 4 hours to complete site</li>
        <li>• <strong>Result:</strong> 10-page site with blog, portfolio, contact forms</li>
        <li>• <strong>Quality:</strong> Professional, customizable, scalable</li>
        <li>• <strong>Can add:</strong> Blog posts, case studies, new services anytime</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-gray-100 rounded-xl p-6 my-8">
      <p class="font-bold mb-3">Durable approach:</p>
      <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-700">
        <li>• <strong>Time:</strong> 15 minutes for landing page</li>
        <li>• <strong>Result:</strong> Great landing page, but nothing else</li>
        <li>• <strong>Quality:</strong> Excellent copy, good design</li>
        <li>• <strong>Can't add:</strong> Blog, additional pages (without workaround)</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 mb-6">
      <strong>Winner:</strong> Framer. Durable can't handle multi-page sites yet.
    </p>

    <h3 class="text-xl font-black mb-4 mt-10">Project 2: Product Landing Page</h3>

    <div class="bg-gray-100 rounded-xl p-6 my-8">
      <p class="font-bold mb-3">Framer approach:</p>
      <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-700">
        <li>• <strong>Time:</strong> 45-60 minutes</li>
        <li>• <strong>Process:</strong> Use AI to generate sections, then manually customize</li>
        <li>• <strong>Result:</strong> Polished, professional page</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-gray-100 rounded-xl p-6 my-8">
      <p class="font-bold mb-3">Durable approach:</p>
      <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-700">
        <li>• <strong>Time:</strong> 10-15 minutes</li>
        <li>• <strong>Process:</strong> Answer questions, AI generates complete page</li>
        <li>• <strong>Result:</strong> Great copy, good design, done</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 mb-6">
      <strong>Winner:</strong> Durable for speed. Framer if you want more customization later.
    </p>
  </section>

  <!-- Pricing Breakdown -->
  <section class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 py-12 border-t border-gray-200">
    <h2 class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl md:text-4xl font-black mb-8 text-gray-900">
      Pricing Breakdown
    </h2>

    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 my-8">
      <div class="bg-gray-100 rounded-xl p-6">
        <h3 class="font-bold mb-3">Framer Pricing</h3>
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-700">
          <li><strong>Free:</strong> Framer domain, limited</li>
          <li><strong>Mini ($15/mo):</strong> Custom domain, basic features</li>
          <li><strong>Pro ($40/mo):</strong> Full CMS, ecommerce, no fees</li>
          <li><strong>Hosting:</strong> Included</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-gray-100 rounded-xl p-6">
        <h3 class="font-bold mb-3">Durable Pricing</h3>
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-700">
          <li><strong>Free:</strong> 3 sites, Durable branding</li>
          <li><strong>Pro ($12/mo):</strong> Custom domain, no branding</li>
          <li><strong>Business ($20/mo):</strong> Multiple sites, analytics</li>
          <li><strong>Hosting:</strong> Included</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>

    <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 mb-6">
      <strong>Value:</strong> Comparable pricing. Durable's Pro tier is slightly cheaper but more limited in scope. Framer costs more but does much more.
    </p>
  </section>

  <!-- Which Should You Choose -->
  <section class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 py-12 border-t border-gray-200">
    <h2 class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl md:text-4xl font-black mb-8 text-gray-900">
      Which Should You Choose?
    </h2>

    <h3 class="text-xl font-black mb-4 mt-10">Choose Framer If:</h3>

    <div class="bg-[#81B29A]/10 border-2 border-[#81B29A] rounded-xl p-6 my-8">
      <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-700">
        <li>• You're building a <strong>complete website</strong> (not just landing page)</li>
        <li>• You need <strong>blogging or CMS</strong> functionality</li>
        <li>• You want <strong>ecommerce</strong> capabilities</li>
        <li>• You care about <strong>design flexibility</strong></li>
        <li>• You're okay investing 1-2 hours to learn</li>
        <li>• You want something <strong>scalable</strong> (can grow with your business)</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <h3 class="text-xl font-black mb-4 mt-10">Choose Durable If:</h3>

    <div class="bg-gray-100 border-2 border-gray-400 rounded-xl p-6 my-8">
      <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-700">
        <li>• You just need a <strong>landing page</strong> (single page is enough)</li>
        <li>• You want to be <strong>online today</strong> (15 minutes from idea to live)</li>
        <li>• You're <strong>not technical</strong> and don't want to learn</li>
        <li>• You care about <strong>copy quality</strong> more than design uniqueness</li>
        <li>• You have <strong>zero budget</strong> for developers/designers</li>
        <li>• You want something that <strong>just works</strong></li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-purple-100 border-l-4 border-purple-600 rounded-r-xl p-6 my-8">
      <p class="font-bold mb-3">Pro tip: Start with Durable, upgrade to Framer later</p>
      <p class="text-gray-700">Launch with Durable (free, 15 minutes). If your business grows, rebuild in Framer. You won't have wasted time or money. Durable is perfect for MVP testing.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- My Verdict -->
  <section class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 py-12 border-t border-gray-200">
    <h2 class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl md:text-4xl font-black mb-8 text-gray-900">
      My Verdict After 6 Weeks
    </h2>

    <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 mb-6">
      I use both for different purposes:
    </p>

    <div class="bg-gray-100 rounded-xl p-6 my-8">
      <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-700">
        <li>• <strong>Durable</strong> — When I have a new business idea and want to test it FAST. Landing page in 15 minutes, drive traffic, see if it converts.</li>
        <li>• <strong>Framer</strong> — When I'm building something real. A business, an agency, a product that needs a proper website with blog, maybe ecommerce.</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 mb-6">
      <strong>The truth:</strong> They're not direct competitors. Durable is for MVPs and quick validation. Framer is for building real businesses online.
    </p>

    <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 mb-6">
      <strong>My recommendation:</strong> Start with Durable (it's free). When you outgrow it, you'll know—because you'll hit Durable's limits. Then switch to Framer.
    </p>

    <div class="text-center my-8">
      <AffiliateLink
        href="https://www.framer.com/"
        className="inline-block bg-purple-600 hover:bg-purple-700 text-white font-black py-3 px-6 rounded-lg mr-2"
      >
        Try Framer Free
      </AffiliateLink>
      <AffiliateLink
        href="https://durable.co/"
        className="inline-block bg-[#81B29A] hover:bg-[#6A9A82] text-white font-black py-3 px-6 rounded-lg"
      >
        Try Durable Free
      </AffiliateLink>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Related Comparisons -->
  <section class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 py-12 border-t border-gray-200">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-black mb-6 text-gray-900">
      More AI Website Builder Comparisons
    </h2>
    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
      <a href="/blog/vs/v0-vs-framer" class="block bg-gray-50 hover:bg-gray-100 rounded-lg p-6 transition-colors">
        <h3 class="font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">v0.dev vs Framer</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-600 text-sm">AI generation vs full website builder.</p>
      </a>
      <a href="/blog/vs/v0-vs-durable" class="block bg-gray-50 hover:bg-gray-100 rounded-lg p-6 transition-colors">
        <h3 class="font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">v0.dev vs Durable</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-600 text-sm">Design vs copy quality comparison.</p>
      </a>
    </div>
  </section>

</Layout>
